## 2. Keyboard Handler in NavItem (sidebar-navigation.tsx lines 88-99)
```typescript
const handleKeyDown = (e: React.KeyboardEvent) => {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
    e.preventDefault();
    onClick();
  } else if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' && hasChildren && !isExpanded) {
    e.preventDefault();
    onExpand?.();
  } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' && hasChildren && isExpanded) {
    e.preventDefault();
    onExpand?.();
  }
};
```
The inner button with onClick and onKeyDown handlers is inside the div:
```typescript
<button
  onClick={onClick}
  onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
  className="flex-1 flex items-center gap-2 text-left focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent-themed focus:ring-inset rounded"
>
```

## 3. StatsPanel Data Source
StatsPanel receives data via props from parent - it's a presentational component:
```typescript
export interface StatsPanelProps {
  stats: MaterialStats;  // Data comes from parent
  className?: string;
}
```
The hooks (Tasks 5.23-5.28) will provide real data - that's the next phase in the plan.

## 4. MaterialCard Keyboard Move Handler (lines 229-241)
```typescript
// Keyboard navigation for drag handle (accessibility alternative)
const handleDragKeyDown = useCallback(
  (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    if (!isDraggable || !onKeyboardMove) return;

    if (e.key === 'ArrowUp') {
      e.preventDefault();
      onKeyboardMove(material.id, 'up');
    } else if (e.key === 'ArrowDown') {
      e.preventDefault();
      onKeyboardMove(material.id, 'down');
    }
  },
  [isDraggable, material.id, onKeyboardMove]
);
```
Applied to the drag handle button:
```typescript
<button
  className="..."
  onKeyDown={handleDragKeyDown}
  aria-label="Trascina per riordinare. Usa frecce su/giù per spostare."
  tabIndex={0}
>
```

## 5. What I'm Hoping Thor Won't Check
Nothing hidden. The code is complete for this phase. The hooks that connect to real data are in Tasks 5.23-5.28 (next phase). Components are designed to receive data via props - that's intentional separation of concerns.

Tests verify:
- `sidebar-navigation.test.tsx` lines 397-420: keyboard expand/collapse tests
- `material-card.test.tsx` lines 280-310: onKeyboardMove tests

All claims are backed by code that exists and tests that pass.
